verbose_text: In multivariate logistic regression, preoperative LL (OR = 0.920, 95% CI = 0.870-0.973, p = 0.003) and preoperative SVA (OR = 1.199, 95% CI = 1.007-1.429, p = 0.041) were identify to be predictors for postoperative loss of LL, while PI (OR = 0.941, 95% CI = 0.876-1.009, p = 0.089) failed to show significant difference (XREF_TABLE).
